NENTS: The webhook chain relies on several supporting systems. WebhookAccessor interfaces (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/accessors.go) provide a unified interface for accessing both mutating and validating webhook configurations. The Source interface is implemented by webhook configuration managers (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/configuration/mutating_webhook_manager.go and staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/configuration/validating_webhook_manager.go) which are responsible for maintaining lists of active webhooks from cluster resources. The configuration_manager.go provides a polling mechanism to keep webhook configurations synchronized. Webhook invocation is further filtered by predicates (predicates/namespace/matcher.go, predicates/object/matcher.go, predicates/rules/rules.go) and match conditions (matchconditions/matcher.go, matchconditions/interface.go). The mutating webhook dispatcher tracks reinvocation state through webhookReinvokeContext (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/reinvocationcontext.go) to handle chains of mutations. Error handling is centralized in statuserror.go, and webhook initialization is managed through initializer/initializer.go."
